snippet: Rebuffing Gov. Rick Scott, a Florida Senate committee proposed using federal money to enroll low-income residents in private insurance as a compromise.
abstract: Florida Senate committee rebuffs Gov Rick Scott's support of Medicaid expansion, rejecting idea and all but ending possibility that state will add more poor people to program; proposes compromise of accepting federal money but using it to put low income people into private insurance plans.

byline.contributor: Christine Jordan Sexton contributed reporting from Tallahassee, Fla.

lead_paragraph: Rebuffing Gov. Rick Scott, a Florida Senate committee proposed using federal money to enroll low-income residents in private insurance as a compromise.

headline.seo: Florida Senate Committee Rejects Medicaid Expansion
headline.main: Medicaid Expansion Is Rejected in Florida
headline.print_headline: Medicaid Expansion Is Rejected In Florida
